For Task 1 of the Digital Literacy Project, I used Canva to design a one-page infographic titled "Digital Literacy — Your Essential 21st Century Skill." 
Canva is a free, browser-based design tool that offers a wide range of templates, icons, and layouts, making it ideal for creating visually appealing content without any prior design experience.
My infographic covers all five key topics from the course: what digital literacy means, useful digital tools for students, building a professional online presence, safe internet practices, and email etiquette. Each section is presented in a colour-coded block with short, easy-to-read bullet points, allowing batchmates to quickly scan and absorb the information.
I chose a blue-and-white colour scheme to keep the design clean and professional.
One interesting thing I discovered while making this was that many free tools I had never used before were available.
One challenge I encountered was fitting all five sections onto a single page without making it look cluttered.
Overall, this task helped me understand how design choices influence how information is received.
